name: Mie Gacoan Batubulan
address: 97F5+96R, Jl. Raya Batubulan, Batubulan, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali, Indonesia
review 1:
The place is nice, the service is fast, affordable, and the food are delicious! Especially the dim sum, the udang keju (cheese shrimp), that's my favorite, they're very tasty!üç•
The downside of this place is the inconsistency in the seasoning of the mie angle (since I always eat mie angel here, Idk with other variants). Sometimes the taste is just right, but other times it's not salty enough. And If you come in the evening, it's very glaring, that's all.

Overall, this place is worth adding to your list of places to visit, especially for those who admire noodle dishes.

name: Gerobak Sushi Batubulan
address: Jl. Raya Batubulan No.98, Batubulan, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80237, Indonesia
review 1:
Nice & affordable sushi's on Batubulan area. They have plenty to choose from and all around twenty thousand rupiah only.
I had the cheesy kana, nori nachos and three other things. They placed on a gallery parking space and have a very cozy ambience despite they are being on the main street.
review 2:
Gerobak Sushi Batubulan is a delightful culinary treasure tucked away in Batubulan. This charming sushi eatery offers a unique and memorable dining experience. The sushi creations here are a testament to the chef's skill and creativity. Each piece is a burst of flavors and freshness that leaves you craving for more.

What truly stands out is the setting. Dining in traditional Balinese-style wooden carts (gerobak) adds a touch of authenticity and charm to the meal. The intimate atmosphere and attentive staff make dining here a pleasure.

While the sushi is exceptional, the pricing is reasonable, making it accessible to a wide range of diners. Gerobak Sushi Batubulan is a must-visit for sushi lovers and anyone looking for a one-of-a-kind dining adventure in Batubulan. My experience here was truly delightful, and I can't wait to return for more sushi artistry.
